ng-the-web/\">Mining the Web: Analysis of Hypertext and Semi Structured Data</a> - S. Chakrabarti. Morgan Kaufmann, 2002.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://courses.ischool.utexas.edu/Lease_Matt/2016/Fall/INF384H/\">INF384H / CS395T / INF350E: Concepts of Information Retrieval (and Web Search)</a> - Matthew Lease (University of Texas at Austin).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.stanford.edu/class/cs276/\">CS 276 / LING 286: Information Retrieval and Web Search</a> - Chris Manning and Pandu Nayak (Stanford University).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.utexas.edu/~mooney/ir-course/\">CS 371R: Information Retrieval and Web Search</a> - Raymond J. Mooney (University of Texas at Austin).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.ucr.edu/~vagelis/classes/CS172/\">CS 172: Introduction to Information Retrieval</a> - Vagelis Hristidis (University of California - Riverside).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www2.sims.berkeley.edu/academics/courses/is240/s06/\">SIMS 240: Principles of Information Retrieval</a> - Ray R. Larson (UC berkeley).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://boston.lti.cs.cmu.edu/classes/11-642/\">11-442 / 11-642: Search Engines</a> - Jamie Callan (CMU).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.jhu.edu/%7Eyarowsky/cs466.html\">600.466: Information Retrieval and Web Agents</a> - David Yarowsky (John Hopkins University).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/spring06/cos435/\">CS 435: Information Retrieval, Discovery, and Delivery</a> - Andrea LaPaugh (Princeton University).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.mpi-inf.mpg.de/departments/databases-and-information-systems/teaching/winter-semester-201516/information-retrieval-and-data-mining/\">Information Retrieval and Data Mining</a> - Dr. Jilles Vreeken , Prof. Dr. Gerhard Weikum (MPI).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h4>Standard IR Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://wiki.dbpedia.org/Downloads2015-10\">DBPedia</a> - Linked data web.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h4>Standard IR Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ir.dcs.gla.ac.uk/resources/test_collections/cran/\">Cranfield Collections</a> - This is one of the first collections in IR domain, however the dataset is too small for any statistical significance analysis, but is nevertheless suitable for pilot runs.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h4>Standard IR Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://ir.dcs.gla.ac.uk/test_collections/gov2-summary.htm\">GOV2 Test Collection</a> - This is one of the largest Web collection of documents obtained from crawl of government websites by Charlie Clarke and Ian Soboroff, using NIST hardware and network, then formatted by Nick Craswel.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h4>Standard IR Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://research.nii.ac.jp/ntcir/data/data-en.html\">NTCIR Test Collection</a> - This is collection of wide variety of dataset ranging from Ad-hoc collection, Chinese IR collection, mobile clickthrough collections to medical collections. The focus of this collection is mostly on east asian languages and cross language information retrieval.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://research.nii.ac.jp/ntcir/permission/ntcir-6/perm-en-CLIR.html\">CLIR Test Collections</a> - This dataset can be used for cross lingual IR between CJKE (Chinese-Japanese-Korean-English) languages. It is suitable for the following tasks:\n<ul>\n<li>Multilingual CLIR</li>\n<li>Bilingual CLIR</li>\n<li>Single Language CLIR</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://research.nii.ac.jp/ntcir/permission/ntcir-6/perm-en-CLQA.html\">Cross Language Q&#x26;A (CLQA) dataset collection</a> - It supports following bi-lingua and mono-lingua:\n<ul>\n<li>Bi-lingua\n<ul>\n<li>Japanese to English.</li>\n<li>Chinese to English.</li>\n<li>English to Japanese.</li>\n<li>English to Chinese.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Mono-lingua\n<ul>\n<li>Chinese to Chinese.</li>\n<li>Japanese to Japanese.</li>\n<li>English to English.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://research.nii.ac.jp/ntcir/permission/ntcir-8/perm-en-ACLIA.html\">Advanced Cross Linugal Information Retrieval and Question Answering (ACLIA)</a> - The dataset is used for the task of cross-lingual question answering but the complexity of the task is higher than CLQA dataset.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2><h4>Standard IR Collections</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.clef-initiative.eu/dataset/test-collection\">Conference and Labs of the Evaluation Forum (CLEF) dataset</a> - It contains a multi-lingual document collection. The test suite includes:\n<ul>\n<li>AdHoc - News Test suite.</li>\n<li>Domain Specific Test Suite - On collections of scientific articles.</li>\n<li>Question Answering Test Suite.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/gary_flake_is_pivot_a_turning_point_for_web_exploration?utm_source=tedcomshare&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=tedspread\">Is Pivot a turning point for web exploration?</a> - Gary Flake, Technical Fellow at Microsoft (TED Talks).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://videolectures.net/wsdm09_dean_cblirs/\">Challenges in Building Large-Scale Information Retrieval Systems</a> - Jeff Dean (WSDM Conference, 2009).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/NFCZuzA4cFc\">Knowledge-based Information Retrieval with Wikipedia</a> - David Wilne (The University of Waikato, 2008).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SghMq1xBJPI&#x26;list=PLdktw5AjQqP2gpQNgHRJaSgEkHiaVLfTi&#x26;index=24\">Music Information Retrieval Using Locality Sensitive Hashing</a> - Steve Tjoa (RackSpace Developers) [This talk shows that IR is not just text and images].</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/u6oqr3gMyxk\">The Functional Web -- The Future of Apps and the Web</a> - Liron Shapira (Box Tech Talk).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Technical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/EnvtsbCfiAI\">Information Experience - Solution to Information Overload on Web</a> - Doug Imbruce (Techcrunch Disrupt)[Doug Imbruce is the Founder of Qwiki, Inc, a technology startup in New York, NY, acquired by Yahoo! in 2013].</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Philosophical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/andreas_ekstrom_the_moral_bias_behind_your_search_results\">The moral bias behind your search results</a> - Andreas Ekström (Swedish Author &#x26; Journalist, TED Talk).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Philosophical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/eli_pariser_beware_online_filter_bubbles?language=en\">Beware online \"filter bubbles\"</a> - Eli Pariser (Author of the Filter Bubble, TED Talk).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-20T18:24:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"harpribot/awesome-information-retrieval","categoryHTML":"<h2>Talks</h2><h4>Philosophical Talks</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/andy_yen_think_your_email_s_private_think_again\">Think your email's private? Think again</a> - Andy Yen (CERN, TED Talk) [Thi